  On the left:</em> Labels lack clarity + tipping too early<br><br>
  <img src="<%= image_path("images/project-opentable/redesign_6.png") %>" class="zoomImages" alt="Missed opportunity for customization‚Äì ‚ÄúWhat if I want to split the tip by portion as well?‚Äù">
  <em>On the left:</em> Missed opportunity for customization‚Äì ‚ÄúWhat if I want to split the tip by portion as well?‚Äù<br><br>


  <h2><strong>Prototype: Reservation Flow</strong></h2>

  <iframe width="438" height="930" src="//invis.io/U9PSJW4W5QN" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe><br><br><br><br>

  <h2><strong>Next Steps</strong></h2>
  While iterating through designs, some ideas came to mind. I would have explored or studied if I had more time to work on this project. <br><br>
  <strong>1. Monitor the payment statuses of your co-diners in real time</strong><br>
  This feature would automatically be on display as soon as an individual has settled his/her portion of the check. He/she will be able to tell whether everyone has already completed their portions, and if not, see whose payments are still ‚Äúin progress.‚Äù<br><br>
  <strong>2. Leave a review for the restaurant</strong><br>
  While waiting for the rest of the diners to complete their payments, the diner will be prompted to leave a review or rate his/her experience at the establishment.<br><br>
  <strong>3. Short walk-through guide upon opening a Tab</strong><br>
  A short walkthrough of the ordering and payment process through OpenTable Tab will be extremely useful to new users. I imagine that this will help them ease into the automated dining process that OpenTable Tab makes available to them.<br><br>

  <h2><strong>Result</strong></h2>
  If OpenTable were to ship this redesign with added features, I hope that in-app payments impact the way restaurateurs run their businesses and allow them to focus on enhancing the overall dining experience for their diners.

